				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">A couple of stupid questions<a name="6464"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 18 03 1:41 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi folks!
<br />

<br />
I've been away from my bard (actually the entire game) for just over a year now.  I got back into it about 3-4 weeks ago for the sole purpose of finally getting my (at the time) main from 49 to 50<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  (I'm an &quot;old school&quot; EQ player, so 50 means a lot to me, haha).  It didn't take long for me to shake the dust off my bard and start playing him again<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  (My main was a Necromancer).
<br />

<br />
When I left the game more than a year ago, my bard was at level 21.  With the help of my main, he had obtained a few pieces of Lambent armor, and a handful of other mediocre items.  Nothing special.  I was going to complete the lambent quests, but I've seen a lot of advice on this board to the contrary, so maybe I'll hold off until I can get Singing Steel (I think that's what it's called).
<br />

<br />
Anyway, my question is one of tactics.  I'm very much a casual player, so most of the time I don't have any time to find a group.  I have to try and rely on myself to level.  Also, I made the mistake (yeah, I think it was a mistake) to go from about level 13 - 21 in Paludal caverns without coming up for air!  Let's put it this way, I don't think Elauriel has a single song from the level 13-21 range yet!  (Bad, Elauriel! &lt;smacks hand&gt;  Bad Bad Elauriel!)
<br />

<br />
So, as you can see, I basically didn't really learn anything about the class during those Paludal levels.  I just sat with a mediocre group for a small handful of hours, and voila! instant level 21!  Absolutely no thought involved whatsoever, as you can imagine (and have probably experienced).
<br />

<br />
Well, now I'm at a real loss.  Firstly, yes I should acquire my new songs obviously.  But there's another problem that's nagging at me:  When I created my Bard, I really didn't know much about the game at all.  I created him around the same time as my main (about 3 years ago), but played the necro almost exclusively.  I've noticed some pretty bad things about my little Wood elf.  For one, his stamina is 67, probably contributing to his fairly low hitpoints (I think my level 9 Frog warrior has more HP than my level 21 bard <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-9.gif" border="0" alt="Crying" hspace="2" />)
<br />

<br />
Ok, now for the actual questions:
<br />
1.  Should I just plain re-roll this character and start all over?
<br />
2.  If so, should I go with a race that has better Stamina?
<br />
3.  If not, what sort of hunting tactics should I be using now at level 21?  Am I too young to start one of the various kiting methods?
<br />

<br />
Thanks a LOT in advance for your help!  Any advice AT ALL would be greatly appreciated.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
