				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple of stupid questions<a name="6467"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 18 03 2:16 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, I'm a wood elf, and I put all my points into STA.  Bards have access to all sorts of great gear, and I twinked the h*ll out of my bard.  All the other stats are easy to get up with the right gear.  It really depends on how many resources you have to equip your bard.  Not everybody has 150k to spend on a lvl 1.
<br />

<br />
Remember, HP's are king.  Eating AE damage on raids can only be offset by tons of hps.  Lvl and resists play a big role in how much damage you take, but believe me, HP is king for survival.  </span></td>
