			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple of stupid questions<a name="6477"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 18 03 3:41 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Boy, a bit to talk about here. I'll try to be brief (hehe right!).
<br />

<br />
Before I tackle your actual questions, let me say I hear ya on PC, it's AWESOME exp, but your skills generally are lacking at the end.  Get your songs, STUDY the songlist so you know what they ALL do (Crital to barding IMHO).  The rest of your skills will be worked out through parking in the bazaar or PoK and working up instruments overnight, or weapon skills over the next 6 or 10 levels in Marus Seru, LoIO etc.  You are in the same boat as most people playing bards today so I wouldn't stress too much about it. Now for your actual questions...
<br />

<br />
1 &amp; 2) My stamina is 79 at 56, and yes, it sucks.  Would I consider rerolling if I were you? Maybe.  A Stamina of 100 is very nice indeed on many levels, and some would say in the endgame it's critical as our HPs don't ever keep up with the tanks we are standing beside, have difficulty avoiding aggro, and have so few gear choices that boost STA.  If you do reroll, Half-elf is the common choice for it's ease etc, but check out the stats for yourself, knowing that on top of STA, DEX and CHA are also arguably important to bards.  I haven't looked over the different classes in a long while so I'll leave that to you.  In the end, if you reroll or keep going it's up to you.  You could get back up to 21 in a heart beat if you did but it's not necessary, most bards have terrible HP at high levels.
<br />

<br />
3) Whether you reroll or not, at level 21, you will continue to group, meleeing and twisting songs to help your group. What songs depends on the needs/deficiencies of the group and will change when one group member is replaced, thus knowing your songlist like the back of your hand.  There is a good discussion that was just brought up in General Bard discussion where I and others went through and helped out with the whole kiting idea, but in general you wouldn't start soloing much until level 26 when you get fear, even then I didn't solo if there was a group to play with, though soloing does fit better with your limited playtime.  Check out that post for how and when to solo.  It's a good question.
<br />

<br />
I hope I haven't confused you and in some way helped to let you make your own decision.  Good luck and keep learning, bards RAWK!
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
